Put the @British chicken thighs{4} in a #mixing bowl{} with the @chermoula spice mix{1}, half the @Greek style natural yoghurt{1/2}, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{pinch}. Massage the chicken until it is well coated.

> TIP: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1/2}(quartered) into ½cm pieces. Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}, cut lengthways into 1cm strips then chop into chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @coriander{1/2%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop. Finely chop the stalks. Zest the @lemon{1/2}(zested). Mix a pinch of lemon zest through the remaining @Greek style natural yoghurt{1/2} in a #small bowl{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a #large saucepan{} on medium heat. Cook the onion until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic and coriander stalks. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} making sure it is coated in the oil. Preheat your #grill{} to its highest setting.

Add the @water{300%ml} to the pan, along with the @chicken stock pot{1/2} and courgette. Bring to the boil. Stir to dissolve the stock pot, then reduce the heat to a simmer and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, put the marinated chicken on a foil-lined #baking tray{}. Pop it under your grill for ~{16-18%minutes}.

> TIP: You want the yoghurt marinade to scorch, so don't be tempted to turn the grill down. It's all about flavour!

Turn the chicken halfway through cooking.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once the rice is ready, stir through the coriander leaves and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add salt, black pepper and more lemon juice if you feel it needs it. Cut the chicken into 1cm thick strips and serve on top of the courgette rice. For a finishing touch, add dollops of lemon yoghurt. Enjoy!